{"type":"data","nodes":[null,{"type":"data","data":[{"post":1,"allPosts":6},{"title":2,"date":3,"slug":4,"content":5},"Idea for tuning LLMs for translation & code","2026-02-28","idea-for-tuning-llms-for-translation-code-4fe837f275f9787f","\u003Cp>Idea for tuning LLMs for translation &#x26; code / RLAIF\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Give one instance of a LLM some rich context and produce a description of the code it would like\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Pass it to a second instance and then have it generate the code\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Pass the code back and have it iterate until the code fits the context.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>You now have (long context, short description, code pairs) which can be used to enrich the training\u003C/p>",[7,11,15,18,22,26,30,34,38],{"title":8,"slug":9,"date":10},"Go fast!","fast","2024-01-01",{"title":12,"slug":13,"date":14},"Consistent Hashing","consistent-hashing","2023-10-26",{"title":16,"slug":17,"date":14},"Rendevous Hashing","rendevous-hashing",{"title":19,"slug":20,"date":21},"Python Coroutines!?!?","py-generator-couroutines","2023-06-11",{"title":23,"slug":24,"date":25},"Lessons from Product Managing","PMing","2023-06-01",{"title":27,"slug":28,"date":29},"Einsum","einsum","2022-03-14",{"title":31,"slug":32,"date":33},"Entropy","entropy","2021-12-28",{"title":35,"slug":36,"date":37},"Try again with sudo: _sudo","_sudo","2021-11-11",{"title":39,"slug":40,"date":37},"Roku & Competition","competition-focus"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
